Theoldramstandslookingdownoverrockslides,stupidlytriumphant.Iblink.Istareinhorror."Scat!"Ihiss."Gobacktoyourcave,gobacktoyourcowshed--whatever."Hecockshisheadlikeanelderly,slow-wittedking,considerstheangles,decidestoignoreme.Istamp.Ihammerthegroundwithmyfists.Ihurlaskull-sizestoneathim.Hewillnotbudge.IshakemytwohairyfistsattheskyandIletoutahowlsounspeakablethatthewateratmyfeetturnssuddeniceandevenImyselfamleftuneasy.Buttheramstays;theseasonisuponus.Andsobeginsthetwelfthyearofmyidioticwar.